  "text": "In the present VLE experiments, a modified Othmer still was used as described by [CITATION_1] . The Othmer still was operated at atmospheric pressure (101.3 kPa). In each experimental run, 50 wt% formaldehyde solution containing 3 wt% 1,3,5-trioxane and 0.2 mol L -1 organic salts was added to the still which was heated in an oil bath. A steady state was usually reached after 1 h of operation. Then samples of the coexisting phases of the quaternary system (formaldehyde ? 1,3,5-trioxane ? organic salt ? water) were taken from vapor and liquid sampling ports and analyzed. Thus, the relative volatility can by defined by",
